    • searchProduct

      public Object searchProduct(List<ElettronicDevice> list, String name, String producer, String min, String max) throws IOException
      This method is used to search for products.
      Parameters:
      list - It is the ElettronicDevice list.
      name - It is the name of a product that is present in the list.
      producer - It is the producer of a product that is present in the list.
      min - It is the minimum price of a product that is on the list.
      max - It is the maximum price of a product that is on the list.
      Returns:
      Returns an ElettronicDevice type list (elprint) where inside there are the products that respect the various parameters passed.
      Throws:
      IOException - Signals that an I/O exception of some sort has occurred.

    • orderProduct

      public int orderProduct(List<ElettronicDevice> elDev, List<ElettronicDevice> buyElDev, String ID, String amount)
      This method is used to buy a product.
      Parameters:
      elDev - It is the ElettronicDevice list.
      buyElDev - It is list of ElettronicDevice for the employee to purchase.
      ID - It is the identification code of the product to be purchased.
      amount - represents the quantity of the product that refers to the ID.
      Returns:
      Returns an integer:
      0 : if the product order has been successful;
      1 : if the quantity of the product ordered is less than zero or greater than the quantity available in the store;
      2 : if the product ID is not found, then the product is not there.
